# Model Fine-tuning and Retraining Plan

This plan outlines the creation of a `model_finetune.py` script to fine-tune existing Forex models using the latest data, avoiding retraining from scratch.

## Proposed Changes

### Forex ML Models Component

#### [NEW] [model_finetune.py](file:///home/job/Desktop/projects/TradeAI/MLmodels/Forex/model_finetune.py)
This script will:
- Accept `symbol` and `interval` as command-line arguments.
- Load the existing model from `/home/job/Desktop/projects/TradeAI/MLmodels/Forex/forex_models/{symbol}/{interval}/model.keras`.
- Fetch the latest 5000 records from TwelveData for the specified symbol and interval.
- Preprocess the data using [build_forex_feature_set](file:///home/job/Desktop/projects/TradeAI/MLmodels/Forex/Data/processing.py#7-51) and `StandardScaler` (consistent with [modeltrain.py](file:///home/job/Desktop/projects/TradeAI/MLmodels/Forex/modeltrain.py)).
- Re-compile the model with a lower learning rate (e.g., 0.0001) for stable fine-tuning.
- Train (fine-tune) for a small number of epochs (e.g., 10-20) to avoid overfitting to new data.
- Save the updated model back to the original path.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- Run `python model_finetune.py --symbol AUDUSD --interval 15min` and verify:
  - The model is loaded successfully.
  - New data is fetched and processed.
  - Training starts and completes without errors.
  - The model file is updated (check timestamp).

### Manual Verification
- Check the output logs to ensure loss decreases during fine-tuning.
- Verify that the model still makes reasonable predictions (using existing inference logic if available).
